Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half
into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Halve the
@bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Pop the
aubergine onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is
hot, roast on the top shelf until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Halfway
through, add the pepper to the aubergine, drizzle with oil and toss together.
Cook for the remaining time.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{} to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.
When boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the
boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}
and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it
sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter it lengthways. Cut
each quarter widthways into 2cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}
(or use a #garlic press{}). Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).
When hot, add the courgette and cook until charred, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn
only every couple of mins - this will result in the courgette picking up some
nice colour. Once cooked, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then transfer to
a #bowl{}.

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Add
the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}. Stir in the
@finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%can}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g},
@tomato puree{30%g}, @Italian style herbs{1%tsp}, @sugar{} and
@water for the sauce{75%ml}. Bring to the boil then reduce the heat and simmer,
stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{7-8%minutes}.

While the sauce simmers, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Drain the
@mozzarella{1} and tear into small pieces. Once everything is ready, stir the
roasted aubergine, pepper, courgette and cooked penne into the sauce. Taste and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Transfer to an #ovenproof dish{}
and top with the mozzarella, Cheddar and @panko breadcrumbs{25%g}. Pop onto
the top shelf of your oven and bake until the cheese is bubbling and golden
brown, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Once the pasta bake is ready, spoon into your #serving bowls{} and tuck in.
Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you've chosen to add bacon to your meal, in the step above,
> before you add the garlic to the pan, add the bacon lardons. Stir-fry
> until golden, 4-5 mins. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after
> handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly. Add the @?british smoked bacon
> lardons{90%g} to the lardons and continue with the step as instructed.